  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_80da95e8a246a931d0410daadd00c557">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Postcards of Cornell University, some used with messages. Includes campus buildings, events, panoramic postcards, postcard books and albums, three folding postcard sets. Some postcards feature people including students. Postcards are both photographic and others are illustrations. Also includes felt postcards and homemade leather postcards. Several of the leather postcards are believed to be the work of Arthur Stickney created for or sent to Corinne Russell.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite audience="internal" id="aspace_d7f4c95fb0c61d03a34721121c169a6c">
    <head>Preferred Citation</head>
<p>Cornell University postcard collection, #47-1-3822. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
  <bioghist audience="internal" id="aspace_e6c9fb30b1a5258fae26a5aaffb5aa70">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Some pPostcards were given to Cynthia Kubas when she was a student by her aunt, Mary Gelsie.</p>  </bioghist>
